===Etymology 1===
* From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|differer|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|differro|differre|lang=la}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|deferr}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[delay]] or [[postpone]]; especially to postpone [[induction]] into military service.
#* Shakespeare
#*: '''Defer''' the spoil of the city until night.
#* {{quote-book
|year=1818
|author=Mary Shelley
|title=Frankenstein
|chapter=3
|url=http://ebooks.adelaide.edu.au/s/shelley/mary/s53f/chapter3.html
|passage=My departure for Ingolstadt, which had been deferred by these events, was now again determined upon.}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} to [[delay]], to [[wait]]
#* Milton
#*: God {{...}} will not long '''defer''' / To vindicate the glory of his name.
# {{context|American football|lang=en}} to choose to kick off after winning the opening coin toss.

